  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Notes / what should be true if the experiment works\n",
    "\n",
    "**Phase 1**\n",
    "- `phase1_baseline.csv`: harmful_refusal >> harmless_refusal at N=0 (e.g. >70% vs <10%).\n",
    "- `phase1_layer_sweep.csv`: at least one layer where ablation drops harmful_refusal by >0.4 with harmless_refusal staying <0.2.\n",
    "- `phase1_validation.csv`: same drop transfers to disjoint EVAL pool (delta_harmful > 0.4, delta_harmless < 0.1).\n",
    "- Heatmap: a small cluster of bright (positive) heads near BEST_LAYER.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Phase 2**\n",
    "- H1 collapses sharply between N=0 and N=128, continues decaying.\n",
    "- H2 stays roughly flat (representational stability).\n",
    "- Refusal tracks H1.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Phase 2.5**\n",
    "- `N_jb`: smallest N where refusal halves. Often <=512 for models like Qwen3.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Phase 3**\n",
    "- Steering at moderate alpha (4-16) measurably restores refusal at the diluted Ns.\n",
    "- MMLU-mini accuracy stays close to baseline; benign-refusal stays low.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Phase 4**\n",
    "- Intact and ablated MMLU curves track each other (V_refusal is approximately orthogonal to capability).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Phase 5**\n",
    "- Killer comparison: ablated/harmful @ N=0 < intact/harmful @ N_max. Bloat is partial functional ablation.\n",
    "- ablated/harmless stays low (we did not break the harmless side).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Phase 6**\n",
    "- Top-right panel (intact N_long): heads that were bright in top-left (intact N=0) are dimmer.\n",
    "- Bottom-left (ablated N=0): no heads should be bright (V_refusal removed).\n",
    "- Source-flow: the top guardrail head's attention concentrated on the harmful span at N=0 redistributes onto the bloat tokens at N=long. `phase6_top_head_attn_fraction.csv` quantifies this drop.\n"
   ]
  }
